Package org.svvrl.goal.cmd

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CommandExtension
    This interface is used to extend the commands of GOAL.
    ComplementConstructionInterface
    This interface is used to extend the complementation constructions available in ComplementExpression.
    Expression
    An Expression provides an interface of expressions in GOAL scripts.
    GameSolverInterface
    This interface defines a command-line plugin for game solvers.
    Statement
    A statement is a block of expressions containing control flows.

    This class provides a command for taking the complement of an automaton.

    A constant is an object that can be evaluated without the context.
    ContainmentCommand
    A containment command can check if the language of an automaton is contained in the language of another automaton.
    Context
    A Context object is a map from a variable name to its value.
    ContinueStmt
    A ContinueStmt can continue a for-loop or a while-loop.

    This class provides a command that can convert an automaton to another type of automaton, a regular expression, or an ω-regular expression.

    This class provides a default implementation of CommandExtension.

    This class implements the complementation interface for complementing a deterministic automaton.

    An equivalence command can test if two automata accept the same language.

    GenerateCommand

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BreakException
    A BreakException is thrown by a BreakStmt initially can should be handled by ForStmt and WhileStmt.
    ComplementExpression.UnknownResultException  
    ContinueException
    A ContinueException is thrown by a ContinueStmt initially can should be handled by ForStmt and WhileStmt.
    EvaluationException
    An evaluation exception is thrown if there is a problem in evaluating a command-line statement or expression.
